'''Abraham Adelaja''' (born 31 January 1988, [[Abuja]]) is a [[Nigeria]]n professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Forward (association football)|striker]] for [[Lusitano F.C. (Portugal)|Lusitano VRSA]].

==Club career==
In July 2013, Adelaja arrived in Portugal to represent [[Farense]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Gigante Adelaja está assegurado |trans-title=Giant Adelaja is secured |url=http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/Nacional/liga_honra/Farense/interior.aspx?content_id=835115 |publisher=Record |date=25 July 2013 |language=Portuguese |accessdate=9 July 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150711132542/http://www.record.xl.pt/Futebol/Nacional/liga_honra/Farense/interior.aspx?content_id=835115 |archivedate=11 July 2015 }}</ref> On 6 July 2015, he moved to fellow [[Segunda Liga]] club [[C.D. Mafra|Mafra]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Mafra apresenta cinco reforços no primeiro dia de trabalho|url=http://www.futebol365.pt/artigo/136294-mafra-apresenta-cinco-reforcos-no-primeiro-dia-de-trabalho/|publisher=Futebol365|date=6 July 2015|language=Portuguese|accessdate=9 July 2015}}</ref>

On 29 August 2016, Adelaja signed a contract with [[Albanian Superliga]] side [[Korabi Peshkopi]] as a free transfer.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://betnews.al/abraham-adelaja-ka-firmosur-sot-per-korabin/|title=Abraham Adelaja ka firmosur sot për Korabin.|publisher=Betnews.al|language=Albanian|date=29 August 2016|accessdate=15 September 2016}}</ref> He was presented on the same day along with [[Nderim Nexhipi]] where he was allocated squad number 88.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://telesport.al/korabi-shton-radhet-prezanton-nexhipin-dhe-adelaja/|title=Korabi shton radhët, prezanton Nexhipin dhe Adelaja|publisher=Telesport.al|language=Albanian|date=29 August 2016|accessdate=15 September 2016}}</ref>

